The police on Thursday arraigned two vagrants in an Apo High Court, Abuja, for allegedly committing murdering a motorcyclist and stealing his Honda motorcycle. The police charged Stefanus Samuel, 24, and Jeremiah Isimiya, 24, who in Mpape, with culpable homicide, stealing and abetting. The prosecutor, Babjide Olanipekun, told the court the defendants committed the offence on Jan. 17, 2016, at Katampe Village, Mpape. Olanipekun alleged that Samuel, who disguised as a passenger, stabbed the bike rider, Bashir Musa, in the neck with a sharp sword and robbed him of his bike. He told the court that the first defendant’s accomplice, Ismiya, thereafter facilitated the sale of the Honda bike, knowing same to have been stolen. Olanipekun said the offence contravened the provisions of sections 1(2) paragraphs A and B of the Robbery and Firearms Special Provisions Act and Section 221 and 91(1) of the Penal Code law. After the charges were read to them, the defendants pleaded not guilty. Defence Counsel, Mrs Princess Oyinye, prayed the court to grant her clients bail, saying they had been in detention in Kuje prison since their arrest in May 2016. Justice Olukayode Adeniyi admitted the defendants to bail in the sum of N2 million each with two sureties in like sum. He ordered that the sureties must be responsible citizens who must reside within the court’s jurisdiction. Adeniyi adjourned the case until June 24, for trial. (NAN)